The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Spain in top spot
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Spain in top spot
                      
	Zurich: India climbed three ranking places to lie at the 148th place in the latest Fifa football rankings released Wednesday.         
	European champions Spain remained top of the world soccer rankings for a fourth straight month after extending their lead over world champions Italy.         
	World Cup qualifying wins over Armenia and Bosnia were enough to keep Vicente Del Bosques side comfortably clear of the Italians, who also enjoyed qualifying victories over Georgia and Cyprus in the past month.         
	Brazil leapfrogged the Netherlands and Croatia into fourth place off the back of their World Cup qualifying draw with Bolivia and away win over Chile.         
	Scotlands hopes of leaving traditional rivals England behind, however, evaporated following a shock 1-0 defeat in Macedonia.         
	Rankings (Top ten)         
	1. (1) Spain; 2. (2) Italy; 3. (3) Germany; 4. (6) Brazil; 5. (4) The Netherlands; 6. (5) Croatia; 7. (7) Argentina; 8. (8) Czech Republic; 9. (12) Russia; 10. (9) Portugal           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                      
